<br>
1-13: Steamfont -- Newbie yard to 4, Kobold camp to 8, outside mines until 12, inside for all of 13<br>
<br>
12-16: Sirens in OOT -- Never anyone out there on Fennin, at least when I did them.  This was right when they nerfed the bard in West Freeport, wanted to kill her, but oh well<br>
<br>
Also 13-18?(19?): Cognoggin -- very boring, but I liked staying near home and torturing faerie creations.  Hits very hard for his level<br>
<br>
16-30: Lake of Ill Omen -- Like everyone else, met great friends here that have lasted a while and when I discovered quad kiting...and dual wizard quad kiting (/wave Aeeon)<br>
<br>
30-35: Various things, FM, OT, tried to quad the cougars in Iceclad, but didn't work.<br>
<br>
35-45: Great Divide -- At 30 or so, you can hunt the Tizmaks and ruin your faction in half an hour.  Groups for Kodiak cave, faction/quest hunting giants, and the such.  40+ I started solo/duo wizard kiting giants (/wave Aeeon again, /wave Dynamite)<br>
Also 34-40: Eastern Wastes -- Quad kiting Walrus/lowest Ulthorks and breezing right through those levels.<br>
<br>
45-50: Cobalt Scar -- Finally, after getting to apprehensive, I started kiting solo wyverns in CS, with wizard friends at times (/wave...all of you anti-druids)<br>
