<br>
circle of force (L34) combined with bof lets you solo time-efficiently. <br>
<br>
before level 34, you have to spend hours root-nuking, or being a tool, sitting in a zone LFG for hours. it really sucks, but hang in there.<br>
<br>
heres how my LFG being-a-tool era went:<br>
1-7 nek forest<br>
8-14 ec and nro<br>
15-20 crocks and orcs in oasis (beware of spec trains)<br>
<br>
at level 20 i went to LOIO, and man, those sarnacks are nice. if you're lucky enough to get in a group here, it goes by very fast, as sarnacks are easy kills for groups. I was lucky, i went from 20 to 28 here in just a few days, yes, a few days. <br>
<br>
at 28, i wasted a few weeks in OT, got occasional groups, ported to NK and stuff when i got those.. blah blah blah<br>
<br>
come level 34, ah yeah. circle of force.<br>
this spell is a 100 % absolute must have. it is almost too mana efficient )<br>
<br>
i started quad kiting thorny succulents and stoneeler cockatrices in OT for a while, they have alot of random-resists tho for BOF, gets kinda time consuming kiting em till they're all snared.<br>
<br>
at level 37, i ventured to velius. pretty nice place, low resists (except cold). try some walruses, they are decent xp until 38, then go to great divide, and quad kite the cave kodiaks. man, these guys are great. they're a pain to pull tho, this is what i did. <br>
I invis'd self, went into the first cave, and positioned self to where when i uninvis, i could agro 3, and then get the hell outta there, lol.<br>
kite em around until they ball up, and BOF em, just use that circle of force, yummy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
oh, heh, you gotta have jboots or sow potions for quadding, otherwise , .... heh. <br>
anyways, i'm level 39, almost 40, still quading those kodiaks<br>
<br>
btw, dont underrate the power of a nice mana pool, it's really frustrating to have to zone out when 4 kodiaks, all at 5 % hp are chasing you. heh. an extra 180 mana from several int points will help greatly with an extra circle to blast em.<br>
<br>
int is at 196, doing fairly well. only run oom on em when i get 2 BOF resists <p>view my lame equip
